    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "It might be a feature of local NTFS but the same attributes are exposed over SMB. So you can enumerate a network path over SMB that contains a OneDrive link which appear as a reparse point but still needs those further checks that the function does. My comment merely tries to confirm that the reparse check can still occur beforehand to reduce the extra Win32 call if the item isnâ€™t a reparse point.",
